It will be a gathering that will have all the cultural trappings of Yewa/Awori. Thousands of guests will roar and clap while masquerades, maiden dancers, drummers and acrobats will display their skills with flair. The Aworis in Lagos and Ogun States will gather on August 17, 2019, to celebrate one of their own, Her Excellency, Engineer Noimot Salako-Oyedele, the Deputy Governor of Ogun State. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Eminent guests expected at the colourful reception, include the Ooni of Ife, His Imperial Majesty, Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi, the Alaafin of Oyo, His Royal Majesty, Oba Lamidi Adeyemi, Awori Obas, other paramount rulers in Yorubaland as well as the governors of Lagos and Ogun states. However, the gathering is not for every Tom, Dick and Harry from Yewa/Aworiland. It is strictly by invitation or ticket. The ticket wonâ€™t tear your pocket: Single is N15, 000.00, while Double is N20, 000.00. 52-year-old Noimot Salako Oyedele is a multi-talented professional with over 30 years of proven records of experience in Consulting, Contracting and Real Estate Sectors. She holds a Masters degree in Public Health Engineering from the Imperial College of Science & Technology London, UK, a Bachelor of Science degree in Civil Engineering from the University of Lagos. An Awori woman from Ado Odo Ota Local Government of Ogun State, Noimot is the daughter of late Professor Lateef Salako who served Ogun State as Chairman, Ogun State Scholarship Board and Chairman Ogun State University Teaching Hospital Board of Management. Prof Salako himself served as Special Adviser to the then Minister of Health, Prof. Olikoye Ransome-Kuti, and was Director-General of the Nigerian Institute of Medical Research for seven years and for a further three years, the Chief Executive Officer of the Federal Vaccine Research Laboratories, Yaba. Awori A Gbe Wa ooo!!!